body:
@hgjung3 thanks! We want to guide the repo in the AutoML direction, to make it easier for people to import their data and train with setting best suited for their own datasets. And I think we are very close to reproducing (and then perhaps exceeding!) the published mAP results.

BTW on that topic I have some news. Two of our training runs just finished, and I discovered that removing the positive weights helps a bit for final mAP. We trained two models at 320 with and without the positive weights (but neither with multi-scale), and we ended up with 48.8 and 49.3 mAP. So based on these results we are going to train with multi-scale now with pw's set to 1.0. It's a tradeoff though, as at the 0.10 conf_thres level the positive weights return better mAP, but at the final testing conf_thres of 0.001 they hurt the results. The positive weight definitely seem to cause overfitting towards the end though as you can see. 

![results](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/26833433/65680578-83d40e80-e057-11e9-93bb-04df0da08f4e.png)
